## 2026-04-05 - Publish readiness checks require manual re-triggering after fixing issues
- Fixed a TDZ bug in `PublishPanel.tsx` where `runReadinessChecks` was referenced before its `useCallback` declaration (line 259 used `runReadinessChecks` defined at line 342 — crashing on first render). Fixed by moving the `runReadinessChecks` useCallback and its `READINESS_TIMEOUT_MS` constant to BEFORE the auto-run effects section.
- Added a second `useEffect` (deps `[tokenChangeKey]`) that auto-rechecks while the Publish tab is already mounted: fires whenever `tokenChangeKey` increments AND a prior check has been run (`checksRunAtKey !== null`). This handles the case where the user edits tokens while on the Publish tab.
- The existing mount-only effect was kept intact to handle the "navigated back to Publish after editing tokens on another tab" case using localStorage comparison.

